  <h1>Engineering Mission: Level 10</h1>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="data">
      <h2>Objective</h2>
      <p>Calculate the structural stress on a metal rod in a truss bridge.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data">
      <h2>Diagnostics Data</h2>
      <p>The force applied to the rod is F = 2 x 10^5 N</p>
      <p>The rod has a cross-sectional area of A = 2 x 10^-4 m^2</p>
      <p>The rod is made of steel with a Young's modulus of E = 2 x 10^11 Pa</p>
      <p>The rod has a length of L = 200 m</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data">
      <h2>Possible Solutions</h2>
      <p>1 x 10^7 Pa</p>
      <p>2 x 10^7 Pa</p>
      <p>4 x 10^7 Pa</p>
      <p>8 x 10^7 Pa</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data correct">
      <h2>Correct Answer</h2>
      <p>2 x 10^7 Pa</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data">
      <h2>Explanation</h2>
      <p>The structural stress on a metal rod can be calculated using the formula Ïƒ = F/A. Plugging in the given values for force, area, and the Young's modulus, the correct answer is 2 x 10^7 Pa</p>
    </div>
